            {/* Source attribution — sits outside all row groups so it
                never picks up row dimming. Top-left, italic, leaves a
                ~25 px gap before the EG row starts at y=50. */}
            <text class="g1-lbl-ann-sm" x="20" y="-12" font-style="italic">As illustrated in Azuma et al., Rev. Mod. Phys. 95, 045006 (2023)</text>

            {/* Classical-bit travelling pulses (drawn at SVG root so they sit
                above their row backgrounds during the active phase). */}
            {/* EG-row classical bits: 4 total, one per BSA, all sliding
                rightward to the next matter qubit. */}
            <circle data-1g-cb="eg0" class="g1-cb-pulse" r="3" cx="0" cy="0" opacity="0"/>
            <circle data-1g-cb="eg1" class="g1-cb-pulse" r="3" cx="0" cy="0" opacity="0"/>
            <circle data-1g-cb="eg2" class="g1-cb-pulse" r="3" cx="0" cy="0" opacity="0"/>
            <circle data-1g-cb="eg3" class="g1-cb-pulse" r="3" cx="0" cy="0" opacity="0"/>
            <circle data-1g-cb="r1"  class="g1-cb-pulse" r="3" cx="0" cy="0" opacity="0"/>
            <circle data-1g-cb="r3"  class="g1-cb-pulse" r="3" cx="0" cy="0" opacity="0"/>
            <circle data-1g-cb="r2"  class="g1-cb-pulse" r="3" cx="0" cy="0" opacity="0"/>
          </svg>

          <ol class="sw-step-list" data-1g-steps>
            <li data-1g-step="1"><strong>1. EG.</strong> Adjacent matter qubits emit photons along the quantum channel; the midpoint BSA performs the Bell-state measurement and heralds a Bell pair across the link.</li>
            <li data-1g-step="2"><strong>2. 1st ES.</strong> R₁ and R₃ run their swaps in parallel; outcomes go forward to R₂ and B.</li>
            <li data-1g-step="3"><strong>3. 2nd ES.</strong> R₂ swaps and ships its outcome to B for the final Pauli correction.</li>
            <li data-1g-step="4"><strong>4. Result.</strong> One long A↔B Bell pair — ready for teleportation or QKD.</li>
          </ol>

          <figcaption>
            Classical bits flow <strong>forward</strong>, one hop at a time. All
            pulses travel at the same horizontal speed, so the long R₂→B leg takes
            visibly longer than the short ones — the latency the memories wait
            through. Each row is a <em>repeat-until-success</em> loop (currently
            shown deterministic; loss retries can be toggled on).
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <Callout label="Pauli frame tracking — one correction at the end, not one per swap">
          <p>
            Each BSM along the chain produces two classical bits that determine which
            of the four Bell states the swap landed on. The naive thing to do is
            apply the corresponding Pauli correction (one of <Math tex="\\{I, X, Z, XZ\\}" />)
            physically at each step. The better thing is to <strong>not apply any
            correction during the chain</strong> and instead XOR each new bit pair
            into a 2-bit <em>Pauli frame</em> held classically at one endpoint —
            metadata that travels alongside the Bell pair but never touches
            the qubits.
          </p>
          <p>
            For a 4-hop chain that means four heralding-BSM outcomes plus six swap-BSM
            bits (two per BSA across three BSAs) all accumulate into a single
            2-bit frame at B. When the pair is finally consumed — at teleportation,
            QKD, or a remote gate — the frame is XOR'd with the consuming
            measurement's outcome bits and one Pauli correction is applied.
            <strong>One physical gate at the end, not seven along the chain.</strong>
            Each avoided physical correction is one less infidelity contribution.
          </p>
        </Callout>

        <Callout label="Why fidelity drops with chain length">
          <p>
            Each Bell pair starts at some fidelity below 1 — heralded entanglement is
            never perfect. Each BSM at a BSA is also imperfect, and each Pauli
            correction sees noise from the classical-message latency relative to the
            memory's coherence time. The end-to-end Bell pair's fidelity is roughly the
            product of the per-link fidelities, multiplied by the BSM and memory
            contributions, so chains of swaps degrade fidelity multiplicatively. This
            is why purification matters at scale — it counters the multiplicative loss
            by spending throughput on cleaner pairs.
          </p>
          <p>
            The first multi-node demo with this pattern is Pompili et al. 2021: a
            three-node NV-centre network — Alice, Bob, and Charlie — all sitting in
            the same lab at QuTech (Delft), with a maximum inter-node distance of
            <strong>7 metres</strong>. Charlie sits between Alice and Bob and acts as
            the swapping BSA, demonstrating on-demand entanglement distribution
            between the non-neighbouring endpoints. The point isn't reach — it's that
            the protocol stack (entanglement generation, swap, fidelity reporting,
            classical signalling) ran end-to-end on a real
            platform <SourceNote id="pompili-science-2021" />.
          </p>
          <p>
            Successive milestones from the same era:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Hermans et al. 2022</strong> — same Delft 3-node hardware, now
              running <strong>qubit teleportation</strong> through the middle node, not
              just entanglement distribution <SourceNote id="hermans-nature-2022" />.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Krutyanskiy et al. 2023</strong> — trapped-ion entanglement
              between two nodes over <strong>230 m</strong> of deployed urban fibre in
              Innsbruck, the first outdoor-fibre heralded
              demo <SourceNote id="krutyanskiy-prl-2023" />.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Knaut et al. 2024</strong> — two SiV-centre nodes at Harvard with
              telecom-O QFC, generating entanglement through a <strong>35 km</strong>
              loop of deployed Boston-area fibre at 17 dB total
              loss <SourceNote id="knaut-nature-2024" />.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            None of these are >3 nodes or km-scale across more than two; multi-node
            swapping chains over real fibre are still the open engineering frontier.
          </p>
        </Callout>
      </section>

      <section id="role" data-nav-section>
        <h2>Network role</h2>
        <p>
          Swapping is the primitive that turns a two-node Bell-pair distribution into a
          full network. The link-layer service ("deliver Bell pair (A, B) on demand")
          inside a single link is a generation problem; getting that pair across more
          than one link is a swapping problem. A repeater is, mechanically, a station
          that holds memories long enough to align swaps — the network engineering is
          all about which pairs to generate when, who fires first, and how to recover
          if any single link's heralding fails.
        </p>
        <p>
          Three follow-on subjects expand on this:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Distribution</strong> covers the link architectures (MM, SR, MS)
            that get a Bell pair onto a single link in the first place. See the
            <strong>distribution</strong> subject.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Purification</strong> trades two noisy Bell pairs for one cleaner
            pair, restoring fidelity that chained swapping erodes. See the
            <strong>purification</strong> subject.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Repeaters</strong> integrate generation, swapping, and purification
            into the 1G / 2G / 3G architectural families. See the
            <strong>repeaters</strong> subject.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </Stack>
  </Center>
</Infographic>

<script type="module" is:inline>
  // Entanglement-swapping animation. Five phases:
  //   1. SETUP    — two Bell pairs (A↔A′, B′↔B) bright; BSM,
  //                 classical channel, bottom result dimmed.
  //   2. BSM      — A′ and B′ photons drop into the apparatus
  //                 along its two diagonals; clouds turn grey;
  //                 top entanglement lines fade; BSM brightens.
  //   3. SEND     — bits (a, b) slide right along the classical
  //                 channel to Bob.
  //   4. CORRECT  — Pauli badge drops onto B; bottom result row
  //                 brightens and the long A↔B wave traces in.
  //   5. HOLD     — everything visible, narrative lines stacked,
  //                 then a short fade-out before the cycle resets.
  const fig = document.querySelector("[data-sw]");
  if (fig) {
    const svg     = fig.querySelector("[data-sw-svg]");
    const aPrime  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-aprime]");
    const bPrime  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-bprime]");
    const aCloud  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-aprime-cloud]");
    const bCloud  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-bprime-cloud]");
    const pairAA  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-pair-aa]");
    const pairBB  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-pair-bb]");
    const pairAB  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-pair-ab]");
    const bsm     = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-bsm]");
    const bits    = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-bits]");
    const bitsTx  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-bits-text]");
    const lock    = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-lock]");
    const lockTx  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-lock-letter]");
    const relayBox = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-relay-box]");
    const stepEls = Array.from(fig.querySelectorAll("[data-sw-step]"));

    const AP_HOME = { x: 359, y: 60 };
    const BP_HOME = { x: 441, y: 60 };
    // BSM apparatus has its own viewBox 640×540 mapped to outer
    // rect (300, 62) → (500, 231). Inner→outer scaling factor:
    // x: 200/640 = 0.3125, y: 169/540 ≈ 0.3130.
    const SX = 200 / 640, SY = 169 / 540;
    const DET = {
      H1: { x: 300 + 130 * SX, y: 62 + 370 * SY },
      V1: { x: 300 + 250 * SX, y: 62 + 370 * SY },
      V2: { x: 300 + 390 * SX, y: 62 + 370 * SY },
      H2: { x: 300 + 510 * SX, y: 62 + 370 * SY },
    };
    const BS_POS = { x: 300 + 320 * SX, y: 62 + 180 * SY };
    const BIT_X_START = 475;
    const BIT_X_END   = 700;
    const LOCK_HOME   = { x: 750, y: 100 };

    // The four Bell-outcome variants. Click-pair labels match the
    // two photon paths through the apparatus; (a, b) is the 2-bit
    // code R sends to Bob; inv is the Pauli Bob applies. Cycled
    // through deterministically.
    const OUTCOMES = [
      { a: 0, b: 0, inv: "I",  clicks: ["H1", "H2"] },
      { a: 1, b: 0, inv: "Z",  clicks: ["V1", "V2"] },
      { a: 0, b: 1, inv: "X",  clicks: ["H1", "V1"] },
      { a: 1, b: 1, inv: "XZ", clicks: ["H1", "V2"] },
    ];
    let outcomeIndex = -1;
    let outcome = OUTCOMES[0];

    function setOpacity(el, op) { el.setAttribute("opacity", String(op)); }
    function setPos(g, x, y) { g.setAttribute("transform", `translate(${x} ${y})`); }
    function setBitsX(x) { bitsTx.setAttribute("x", String(x)); }
    function highlightStep(n) {
      for (const el of stepEls) {
        el.classList.toggle("sw-step--active", Number(el.dataset.swStep) === n);
      }
    }
    function ease(t) {
      return t < 0.5 ? 4*t*t*t : 1 - Math.pow(-2*t + 2, 3) / 2;
    }
    function twoLeg(start, mid, end, t) {
      if (t < 0.4) {
        const k = t / 0.4;
        return { x: start.x + (mid.x - start.x) * k, y: start.y + (mid.y - start.y) * k };
      }
      const k = (t - 0.4) / 0.6;
      return { x: mid.x + (end.x - mid.x) * k, y: mid.y + (end.y - mid.y) * k };
    }

    function pickCycleParams() {
      outcomeIndex = (outcomeIndex + 1) % OUTCOMES.length;
      outcome = OUTCOMES[outcomeIndex];
      bitsTx.textContent = `(${outcome.a}, ${outcome.b})`;
      lockTx.textContent = outcome.inv;
      aCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-teal)");
      bCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-teal)");
      setPos(aPrime, AP_HOME.x, AP_HOME.y);
      setPos(bPrime, BP_HOME.x, BP_HOME.y);
    }

    const reducedMotion = matchMedia("(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)").matches;

    if (reducedMotion) {
      pickCycleParams();
      setOpacity(aPrime, 0); setOpacity(bPrime, 0);
      setOpacity(pairAA, 0); setOpacity(pairBB, 0);
      setOpacity(bsm, 0.22);
      setOpacity(bits, 0); setOpacity(lock, 0);
      setOpacity(relayBox, 0);
      setOpacity(pairAB, 1);
      pairAB.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "0");
      highlightStep(5);
    } else {
      const T_SETUP   = 1400;
      const T_DROP    = 1300;
      const T_MEASURE =  900;
      const T_SEND    = 1700;
      const T_UNLOCK  = 2400;   // Pauli badge dropping onto B (step 4
                                // in the list) — was 1100 ms, too fast.
      const T_TRACE   = 1100;
      const T_HOLD    = 2600;
      const T_PAUSE   =  400;
      const T_TOTAL = T_SETUP + T_DROP + T_MEASURE + T_SEND + T_UNLOCK + T_TRACE + T_HOLD + T_PAUSE;

      let running = false;
      let cycleStart = 0;

      function frame(now) {
        if (!running) return;
        const elapsed = now - cycleStart;
        let t0 = T_SETUP;

        if (elapsed < t0) {
          // Phase 1 — setup
          highlightStep(1);
          setOpacity(aPrime, 1); setOpacity(bPrime, 1);
          setPos(aPrime, AP_HOME.x, AP_HOME.y);
          setPos(bPrime, BP_HOME.x, BP_HOME.y);
          aCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-teal)");
          bCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-teal)");
          setOpacity(pairAA, 0.95);
          setOpacity(pairBB, 0.95);
          setOpacity(bsm, 0.22);
          setOpacity(bits, 0);
          setOpacity(lock, 0);
          setOpacity(relayBox, 0.55);
          setOpacity(pairAB, 0);
          pairAB.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "1");
          const t = elapsed / T_SETUP;
        } else if (elapsed < (t0 += T_DROP)) {
          // Phase 2a — A′ and B′ drop into BSM apparatus
          highlightStep(2);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - T_DROP)) / T_DROP;
          const e = ease(t);
          const cClick = outcome.clicks[0];
          const bClick = outcome.clicks[1];
          const aEnd = DET[cClick];
          const bEnd = DET[bClick];
          const aPos = twoLeg(AP_HOME, BS_POS, aEnd, e);
          const bPos = twoLeg(BP_HOME, BS_POS, bEnd, e);
          setPos(aPrime, aPos.x, aPos.y);
          setPos(bPrime, bPos.x, bPos.y);
          setOpacity(bsm, 0.22 + 0.78 * Math.min(1, e * 1.5));
          setOpacity(pairAA, 0.95 * Math.max(0, 1 - e * 1.6));
          setOpacity(pairBB, 0.95 * Math.max(0, 1 - e * 1.6));
          if (e > 0.15) {
            aCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-spent)");
            bCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-spent)");
          }
        } else if (elapsed < (t0 += T_MEASURE)) {
          // Phase 2b — measurement clicks
          highlightStep(2);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - T_MEASURE)) / T_MEASURE;
          const e = ease(t);
          setOpacity(aPrime, Math.max(0, 1 - e * 2));
          setOpacity(bPrime, Math.max(0, 1 - e * 2));
          setOpacity(pairAA, 0); setOpacity(pairBB, 0);
          setOpacity(bsm, 1);
          setOpacity(bits, Math.min(1, (e - 0.2) * 2));
          setBitsX(BIT_X_START);
        } else if (elapsed < (t0 += T_SEND)) {
          // Phase 3 — bits slide along classical channel
          highlightStep(3);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - T_SEND)) / T_SEND;
          setOpacity(aPrime, 0); setOpacity(bPrime, 0);
          setOpacity(bsm, 0.5);
          setOpacity(bits, 1);
          setBitsX(BIT_X_START + (BIT_X_END - BIT_X_START) * t);
        } else if (elapsed < (t0 += T_UNLOCK)) {
          // Phase 4a — Pauli badge drops onto B
          highlightStep(4);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - T_UNLOCK)) / T_UNLOCK;
          const e = ease(t);
          setBitsX(BIT_X_END);
          setOpacity(bits, Math.max(0, 1 - e * 1.4));
          const ix_start = BIT_X_END, iy_start = 235;
          const ix_end = LOCK_HOME.x, iy_end = LOCK_HOME.y;
          const ix = ix_start + (ix_end - ix_start) * e;
          const iy = iy_start + (iy_end - iy_start) * e;
          setPos(lock, ix, iy);
          setOpacity(lock, Math.min(1, e * 2));
        } else if (elapsed < (t0 += T_TRACE)) {
          // Phase 4b — long A↔B Bell pair traces in on the SAME row
          // as A and B. The dashed relay-R box dissolves at the same
          // time so the line spans the row cleanly; the BSM apparatus
          // dims back down too.
          highlightStep(5);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - T_TRACE)) / T_TRACE;
          const e = ease(t);
          setOpacity(pairAB, 1);
          pairAB.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", String(1 - e));
          setOpacity(lock, Math.max(0, 1 - e * 1.6));
          setOpacity(bsm, 0.5 - 0.28 * e);
          setOpacity(relayBox, 0.55 * (1 - e));
        } else if (elapsed < T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE) {
          // Phase 5 — hold final state
          highlightStep(5);
          setOpacity(pairAB, 1);
          pairAB.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "0");
          setOpacity(lock, 0);
          setOpacity(bsm, 0.22);
          setOpacity(relayBox, 0);
        } else if (elapsed < T_TOTAL) {
          const t = (elapsed - (T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE)) / T_PAUSE;
          const a = Math.max(0, 1 - t);
        } else {
          cycleStart = now;
          pickCycleParams();
        }
        requestAnimationFrame(frame);
      }

      pickCycleParams();
      const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
        for (const entry of entries) {
          if (entry.isIntersecting && !running) {
            running = true;
            cycleStart = performance.now();
            pickCycleParams();
            requestAnimationFrame(frame);
          } else if (!entry.isIntersecting) {
            running = false;
          }
        }
      });
      observer.observe(fig);
    }
  }
</script>

<script type="module" is:inline>
  // Canonical 1G repeater animation. Four phases, walking down the four
  // rows of the stacked diagram so the reader sees time progression.
  // Each row remains visible (history) and dims to 0.45 once its phase
  // ends — the currently-active row stays at 1.0.
  //
  // Per-segment state machines are scaffolded so loss retries can be
  // toggled on by flipping CONFIG.lossEnabled (and dialling the success
  // probabilities below 1.0). With successP = 1.0 the cycle is
  // deterministic: every EG link heralds first try, every swap BSM
  // succeeds first try, and the animation plays linearly.
  function initOnegen(fig) {
    const svg     = fig.querySelector("[data-1g-svg]");
    const rows    = [1, 2, 3, 4].map((n) => svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-row="${n}"]`));
    const photons = Array.from({ length: 8 }, (_, i) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-photon="${i}"]`));
    const bsas    = Array.from({ length: 4 }, (_, i) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-bsa="${i}"]`));
    const bmR1    = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r1]");
    const bmR3    = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r3]");
    const bmR2    = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r2]");
    const bmR1Pulse = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r1-pulse]");
    const bmR3Pulse = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r3-pulse]");
    const bmR2Pulse = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r2-pulse]");
    const bmR1Herald = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r1-herald]");
    const bmR3Herald = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r3-herald]");
    const bmR2Herald = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r2-herald]");
    // The two matter qubits that flank each BSM meter — they light up
    // together with the meter when the BSM fires.
    const bsmQ = {
      r1: [svg.querySelector('[data-1g-bsm-q="r1L"]'), svg.querySelector('[data-1g-bsm-q="r1R"]')],
      r3: [svg.querySelector('[data-1g-bsm-q="r3L"]'), svg.querySelector('[data-1g-bsm-q="r3R"]')],
      r2: [svg.querySelector('[data-1g-bsm-q="r2L"]'), svg.querySelector('[data-1g-bsm-q="r2R"]')],
    };
    const ent2    = ["2a", "2b", "2c", "2d"].map((k) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-ent-${k}]`));
    const ent3    = ["3a", "3b"].map((k) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-ent-${k}]`));
    const entFinal = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-ent-final]");
    const cbR1    = svg.querySelector('[data-1g-cb="r1"]');
    const cbR3    = svg.querySelector('[data-1g-cb="r3"]');
    const cbR2    = svg.querySelector('[data-1g-cb="r2"]');
    const stepEls = Array.from(fig.querySelectorAll("[data-1g-step]"));

    // ---------------- Loss-toggle scaffolding ----------------
    // Currently disabled — successP = 1.0 means every attempt heralds
    // first try, so the cycle is deterministic and plays linearly.
    // When ready to show loss: flip lossEnabled to true and drop the
    // success probabilities; the animation loop will spend extra cycles
    // showing photons disappear without herald, etc.
    const CONFIG = {
      lossEnabled: false,
      egSuccessP:  1.0,   // P(herald) per EG attempt; ~0.5 realistic
      esSuccessP:  1.0,   // P(success) per matter-qubit BSM; ~0.95 realistic
    };
    function attempt(p) {
      return CONFIG.lossEnabled ? (Math.random() < p) : true;
    }

    // Per-segment state. Each segment owns its own attempt counter and
    // last-outcome flag. With successP = 1.0 attempts always succeed
    // and the phase advances immediately; with lower successP, the
    // animation can spin in the current phase until allSettled() is
    // true. (Retry rendering is scaffolded but not yet active.)
    const egSegs = [0,1,2,3].map(() => ({ heralded: false, attempts: 0 }));
    const es1Segs = ["R1", "R3"].map(() => ({ done: false, attempts: 0 }));
    const es2Segs = ["R2"].map(() => ({ done: false, attempts: 0 }));
    function resetSegs() {
      egSegs.forEach((s) => { s.heralded = false; s.attempts = 0; });
      es1Segs.forEach((s) => { s.done = false; s.attempts = 0; });
      es2Segs.forEach((s) => { s.done = false; s.attempts = 0; });
    }
    function rollPhase1() { egSegs.forEach((s) => { s.attempts++; s.heralded = attempt(CONFIG.egSuccessP); }); }
    function rollPhase2() { es1Segs.forEach((s) => { s.attempts++; s.done = attempt(CONFIG.esSuccessP); }); }
    function rollPhase3() { es2Segs.forEach((s) => { s.attempts++; s.done = attempt(CONFIG.esSuccessP); }); }

    function setOpacity(el, op) { el && el.setAttribute("opacity", String(op)); }
    function setPos(el, x, y) { el && el.setAttribute("cx", String(x)); el && el.setAttribute("cy", String(y)); }
    function setFilter(el, f) { if (el) el.style.filter = f || "none"; }
    // Shared amber glow recipe — same colours as the meterFilter() used
    // in AnimatedOpsPrimitives. t ∈ [0,1] modulates the strength so the
    // glow can pulse with the BSM firing.
    function glow(t) {
      const a = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, t));
      const r1 = (4 + 4 * a).toFixed(1);
      const r2 = (4 + 4 * a).toFixed(1);
      return `drop-shadow(0 0 ${r1}px #f59e0b) drop-shadow(0 0 ${r2}px #fbbf24)`;
    }
    function residualGlow() { return "drop-shadow(0 0 3px rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.4))"; }
    function highlightStep(n) {
      for (const el of stepEls) {
        el.classList.toggle("sw-step--active", Number(el.dataset["1gStep"]) === n);
      }
    }

    // Per-photon segment geometry: from matter qubit edge (x0) to BSA
    // facing edge (x1). All at y=70 on the horizontal channel.
    const SEG = [
      { x0: 141, x1: 209 },  // A → BSA0 (right)
      { x0: 309, x1: 237 },  // R₁L → BSA0 (left)
      { x0: 347, x1: 417 },  // R₁R → BSA1 (right)
      { x0: 515, x1: 445 },  // R₂L → BSA1 (left)
      { x0: 553, x1: 623 },  // R₂R → BSA2 (right)
      { x0: 721, x1: 651 },  // R₃L → BSA2 (left)
      { x0: 759, x1: 831 },  // R₃R → BSA3 (right)
      { x0: 927, x1: 859 },  // B   → BSA3 (left)
    ];
    const PHOTON_HOME = SEG.map((s) => ({ x: s.x0, y: 70 }));
    const PHOTON_END  = SEG.map((s) => ({ x: s.x1, y: 70 }));
    const fibres = Array.from({ length: 8 }, (_, i) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-fibre="${i}"]`));
    const mpWaves = Array.from({ length: 8 }, (_, i) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-mp-wave="${i}"]`));
    // Generate a wavy SVG path d-string from (x0,y) to (x1,y). Amplitude
    // and half-wavelength match the matter-photon bond used on the home
    // page's ops-primitives.svg.
    function genWavyD(x0, x1, y, halfWl, amp) {
      halfWl = halfWl || 8;
      amp = amp || 3.5;
      const dist = Math.abs(x1 - x0);
      if (dist < 0.5) return "M " + x0.toFixed(2) + "," + y;
      const dir = x1 > x0 ? 1 : -1;
      const n = Math.max(1, Math.round(dist / halfWl));
      const step = dir * (dist / n);
      const s2 = (step / 2).toFixed(2);
      const sw = step.toFixed(2);
      let d = "M " + x0.toFixed(2) + "," + y + " q " + s2 + "," + (-amp) + " " + sw + ",0";
      for (let i = 1; i < n; i++) d += " t " + sw + ",0";
      return d;
    }
    function setFibreToPhoton(i, photonX) {
      const f = fibres[i];
      if (!f) return;
      f.setAttribute("x1", String(photonX));
    }
    function setWavyToPhoton(i, photonX) {
      const w = mpWaves[i];
      if (!w) return;
      w.setAttribute("d", genWavyD(SEG[i].x0, photonX, 70));
    }
    function resetFibresFull() {
      // Photon at matter edge → fibre spans the full matter→BSA gap.
      fibres.forEach((f, i) => f && f.setAttribute("x1", String(SEG[i].x0)));
    }
    function resetWavyEmpty() {
      // No matter-photon bond drawn yet (photon hasn't been emitted).
      mpWaves.forEach((w, i) => w && w.setAttribute("d", "M " + SEG[i].x0 + ",70"));
    }
    // EG classical-bit polylines: drop from BSA (y=86) down to the
    // classical line (y=105), slide rightward to the next matter qubit,
    // then rise UP into that box's bottom edge. One bit per BSA.
    const EG_BIT_PATHS = [
      [{x:223,y:86},{x:223,y:105},{x:328,y:105},{x:328,y:83}],  // BSA0 → R₁ box
      [{x:431,y:86},{x:431,y:105},{x:534,y:105},{x:534,y:83}],  // BSA1 → R₂ box
      [{x:637,y:86},{x:637,y:105},{x:740,y:105},{x:740,y:83}],  // BSA2 → R₃ box
      [{x:845,y:86},{x:845,y:105},{x:938,y:105},{x:938,y:87}],  // BSA3 → B box
    ];
    const cbEG = Array.from({ length: 4 }, (_, i) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-cb="eg${i}"]`));
    // Polyline helpers — used by both EG and swap bits.
    function polyLen(pts) {
      let L = 0;
      for (let i = 1; i < pts.length; i++) {
        L += Math.hypot(pts[i].x - pts[i-1].x, pts[i].y - pts[i-1].y);
      }
      return L;
    }
    function polyAt(pts, d) {
      for (let i = 1; i < pts.length; i++) {
        const sl = Math.hypot(pts[i].x - pts[i-1].x, pts[i].y - pts[i-1].y);
        if (d <= sl) {
          const k = d / sl;
          return {
            x: pts[i-1].x + (pts[i].x - pts[i-1].x) * k,
            y: pts[i-1].y + (pts[i].y - pts[i-1].y) * k,
          };
        }
        d -= sl;
      }
      const last = pts[pts.length - 1];
      return { x: last.x, y: last.y };
    }
    function setBitAt(el, p) {
      el.setAttribute("cx", String(p.x));
      el.setAttribute("cy", String(p.y));
    }

    // Classical-bit pulse geometry. All swap-row pulses flow
    // forward (rightward, toward B) at the same speed — so a long
    // R₂→B leg visibly takes more time than a short R₁→R₂ leg.
    // That's the latency story: classical-message time scales with
    // distance, and the matter qubits hold while it's in flight.
    //
    // EG row: short vertical hops from each pBSM up to the matter
    // row. ES1 and ES2: horizontal hops starting at the right edge
    // of each "Bell measurement" label, ending at the next-forward
    // node (R₂ for R₁; B for R₃; B for R₂).
    // Swap-row bit polylines (visual coords after translate(0,-130) on
    // rows 2/3/4). Each path: meter bottom → drop to classical line →
    // slide rightward to destination box's x-centre → rise UP into the
    // destination box bottom.
    const CB_PATHS = {
      r1: { points: [{x:328,y:184},{x:328,y:225},{x:534,y:225},{x:534,y:208}] },
      r3: { points: [{x:740,y:184},{x:740,y:225},{x:938,y:225},{x:938,y:212}] },
      r2: { points: [{x:534,y:313},{x:534,y:355},{x:938,y:355},{x:938,y:342}] },
    };
    for (const k of Object.keys(CB_PATHS)) CB_PATHS[k].len = polyLen(CB_PATHS[k].points);
    const CB_SPEED = 0.20;  // px/ms — picked so R₂→B takes ~2.3 s
    const CB_DUR = {
      r1: CB_PATHS.r1.len / CB_SPEED,
      r3: CB_PATHS.r3.len / CB_SPEED,
      r2: CB_PATHS.r2.len / CB_SPEED,
    };
    const CB_DUR_MAX_ES1 = Math.max(CB_DUR.r1, CB_DUR.r3);
    function moveCbBySpeed(key, elapsedMs) {
      const p = CB_PATHS[key];
      const el = key === "r1" ? cbR1 : key === "r3" ? cbR3 : cbR2;
      setBitAt(el, polyAt(p.points, elapsedMs * CB_SPEED));
    }

    function ease(t) {
      return t < 0.5 ? 4*t*t*t : 1 - Math.pow(-2*t + 2, 3) / 2;
    }

    const reducedMotion = matchMedia("(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)").matches;

    if (reducedMotion) {
      // Static end state: all rows fully visible.
      rows.forEach((r) => setOpacity(r, 1));
      ent2.forEach((e) => e && e.setAttribute("opacity", "1"));
      ent3.forEach((e) => e && e.setAttribute("opacity", "1"));
      entFinal && entFinal.setAttribute("opacity", "1");
      highlightStep(4);
    } else {
      const T_EG_EMIT   = 1400;   // photons emit + travel toward pBSMs
      const T_EG_MEAS   =  900;   // pBSMs pulse, herald bulbs flash
      const T_EG_CLASS  = 1200;   // classical herald travels back up
      const T_ES1_FADE  =  600;   // entanglement curves fade in (row 2)
      const T_ES1_SETTLE =  800;  // freshly-distributed bonds pulsate
      const T_ES1_PREP  = T_ES1_FADE + T_ES1_SETTLE;
      const T_ES1_BSM   =  900;   // BM boxes at R₁, R₃ pulse
      // Classical-bit budgets are derived from CB_SPEED + path length
      // so all pulses move at the same px/ms. R₁→R₂ and R₃→B are
      // similar length (~150 px); R₂→B is much longer (~350 px). The
      // budget = max-path-time + 200 ms tail so the longest pulse can
      // finish and linger briefly before the phase advances.
      const T_ES1_CLASS = Math.ceil(CB_DUR_MAX_ES1) + 200;
      const T_ES2_FADE  =  600;   // entanglement curves fade in (row 3)
      const T_ES2_SETTLE =  800;  // freshly-distributed bonds pulsate
      const T_ES2_PREP  = T_ES2_FADE + T_ES2_SETTLE;
      const T_ES2_BSM   =  900;   // BM box at R₂ pulses
      const T_ES2_CLASS = Math.ceil(CB_DUR.r2) + 200;
      const T_RESULT_FADE   =  800;   // long A↔B Bell pair fades in
      const T_RESULT_SETTLE =  800;   // and then pulsates once
      const T_RESULT    = T_RESULT_FADE + T_RESULT_SETTLE;
      const T_HOLD      = 3600;
      const T_PAUSE     =  400;
      const PHASE1 = T_EG_EMIT + T_EG_MEAS + T_EG_CLASS;
      const PHASE2 = T_ES1_PREP + T_ES1_BSM + T_ES1_CLASS;
      const PHASE3 = T_ES2_PREP + T_ES2_BSM + T_ES2_CLASS;
      const PHASE4 = T_RESULT;
      const T_TOTAL = PHASE1 + PHASE2 + PHASE3 + PHASE4 + T_HOLD + T_PAUSE;

      let running = false;
      let paused = false;
      let cycleStart = 0;
      let pausedAt = 0;
      // Playback speed multiplier. virtual_elapsed = (now - cycleStart) * speed.
      // The user toolbar cycles through 0.5×, 0.75×, 1×.
      let speed = 1.0;

      // Phase boundaries used by the step controls. Stepping snaps the
      // virtual clock to one of these; the user gets four discrete
      // "frames" of the protocol — start of EG, start of 1st ES,
      // start of 2nd ES, start of Result — plus the hold state.
      const PHASE_STARTS = [
        0,
        PHASE1,
        PHASE1 + PHASE2,
        PHASE1 + PHASE2 + PHASE3,
        PHASE1 + PHASE2 + PHASE3 + PHASE4,
      ];

      function pickCycleParams() {
        resetSegs();
        rollPhase1();
        rollPhase2();
        rollPhase3();
      }

      function phaseAt(elapsed) {
        if (elapsed < PHASE1) return "EG";
        if (elapsed < PHASE1 + PHASE2) return "1st ES";
        if (elapsed < PHASE1 + PHASE2 + PHASE3) return "2nd ES";
        if (elapsed < PHASE1 + PHASE2 + PHASE3 + PHASE4) return "Result";
        return "Hold";
      }

      // Pure render — sets element states based on a virtual elapsed
      // time in [0, T_TOTAL]. No requestAnimationFrame, no time math
      // beyond what's needed for sub-phase interpolation. The transport
      // controls call this with arbitrary clock positions.
      function renderAt(elapsed) {
        let t0 = 0;
        // -------- Phase 1 — EG --------
        if (elapsed < (t0 += PHASE1)) {
          highlightStep(1);
          setOpacity(rows[0], 1);
          setOpacity(rows[1], 0.22);
          setOpacity(rows[2], 0.22);
          setOpacity(rows[3], 0.22);
          ent2.forEach((e) => e && e.setAttribute("opacity", "0"));
          ent3.forEach((e) => e && e.setAttribute("opacity", "0"));
          entFinal && entFinal.setAttribute("opacity", "0");

          const local = elapsed - (t0 - PHASE1);
          if (local < T_EG_EMIT) {
            // 1a: photons emit from each matter qubit and fly along the
            // channel toward the BSA. The matter-photon wavy bond grows
            // from the qubit edge to the photon's current position; the
            // blue fibre line from photon to BSA shrinks correspondingly.
            const t = local / T_EG_EMIT;
            const e = ease(t);
            photons.forEach((ph, i) => {
              if (!ph) return;
              const s = SEG[i];
              const curX = s.x0 + (s.x1 - s.x0) * e;
              setPos(ph, curX, 70);
              setOpacity(ph, 1);
              setWavyToPhoton(i, curX);
              setOpacity(mpWaves[i], 1);
            });
            bsas.forEach((b) => setFilter(b, "none"));
            cbEG.forEach((c) => setOpacity(c, 0));
          } else if (local < T_EG_EMIT + T_EG_MEAS) {
            // 1b: photons arrive at the BSA. BSA fuzzy-glows. The wavy
            // matter-photon bond fades (entanglement transferred to the
            // BSA's measurement); the fibre is already at zero length.
            const t = (local - T_EG_EMIT) / T_EG_MEAS;
            photons.forEach((ph, i) => {
              setOpacity(ph, Math.max(0, 1 - t * 2));
              setPos(ph, SEG[i].x1, 70);
            });
            mpWaves.forEach((w) => setOpacity(w, Math.max(0, 1 - t * 2)));
            const pulse = Math.sin(t * Math.PI);
            bsas.forEach((b, i) => {
              if (!egSegs[i].heralded) { setFilter(b, "none"); return; }
              setFilter(b, glow(pulse));
            });
          } else {
            // 1c: BSA glow settles to residual; wavy bonds are gone, the
            // classical bit slides rightward from each BSA to the next
            // matter qubit along the classical channel.
            const t = (local - T_EG_EMIT - T_EG_MEAS) / T_EG_CLASS;
            photons.forEach((ph) => setOpacity(ph, 0));
            mpWaves.forEach((w) => setOpacity(w, 0));
            bsas.forEach((b, i) => setFilter(b, egSegs[i].heralded ? residualGlow() : "none"));
            // One bit per BSA. Polyline: drop down stub from BSA, slide
            // rightward along the classical line, rise UP into the next
            // matter qubit's box. Bit reaches the destination at 80% of
            // the phase then lingers there for the remaining 20%.
            cbEG.forEach((c, i) => {
              if (!c) return;
              if (!egSegs[i].heralded) { setOpacity(c, 0); return; }
              setOpacity(c, 1);
              const path = EG_BIT_PATHS[i];
              const reach = Math.min(1, t / 0.80);
              setBitAt(c, polyAt(path, reach * polyLen(path)));
            });
          }
        }
        // -------- Phase 2 — 1st ES --------
        else if (elapsed < (t0 += PHASE2)) {
          highlightStep(2);
          setOpacity(rows[0], 0.45);
          setOpacity(rows[1], 1);
          setOpacity(rows[2], 0.22);
          setOpacity(rows[3], 0.22);
          mpWaves.forEach((w) => setOpacity(w, 0));
          cbEG.forEach((c) => setOpacity(c, 0));
          // Restore fibres to full length so the dimmed EG row reads as
          // "channels still in place, ready for the next round".
          resetFibresFull();
          resetWavyEmpty();
          // EG-row glows persist (those qubits are still entangled — the
          // row simply dims globally) so don't clear bsa/mq filters here.

          const local = elapsed - (t0 - PHASE2);
          if (local < T_ES1_PREP) {
            // 2a: bonds fade in, then pulsate briefly so the reader
            // registers the distributed entanglement before the BSM
            // fires. Stroke-width sine bump at full opacity.
            setOpacity(cbR1, 0); setOpacity(cbR3, 0);
            setOpacity(bmR1Pulse, 0); setOpacity(bmR3Pulse, 0);
            setFilter(bmR1Herald, "none"); setFilter(bmR3Herald, "none");
            if (local < T_ES1_FADE) {
              const t = local / T_ES1_FADE;
              ent2.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("opacity", String(t)));
              ent2.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.7"));
            } else {
              const t = (local - T_ES1_FADE) / T_ES1_SETTLE;
              const w = 1.7 + 1.6 * Math.sin(t * Math.PI);  // 0 → peak → 0 sine bump
              ent2.forEach((p) => {
                if (!p) return;
                p.setAttribute("opacity", "1");
                p.setAttribute("stroke-width", String(w));
              });
            }
          } else if (local < T_ES1_PREP + T_ES1_BSM) {
            // BSM firing: meter + the two measured qubits fuzzy-glow.
            // BM-box stroke pulses as a secondary cue.
            ent2.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("opacity", "1"));
            const t = (local - T_ES1_PREP) / T_ES1_BSM;
            const pulse = Math.sin(t * Math.PI);
            const w = 1.2 + 1.6 * pulse;
            if (bmR1) bmR1.setAttribute("stroke-width", String(w));
            if (bmR3) bmR3.setAttribute("stroke-width", String(w));
            // Reset entanglement bond stroke after the pulsate beat.
            ent2.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.7"));
            setOpacity(bmR1Pulse, pulse);
            setOpacity(bmR3Pulse, pulse);
            const g = glow(pulse);
            setFilter(bmR1Herald, g);
            setFilter(bmR3Herald, g);
            bsmQ.r1.forEach((q) => setFilter(q, g));
            bsmQ.r3.forEach((q) => setFilter(q, g));
          } else {
            // Classical bits travel onward; meter glow settles to residual.
            if (bmR1) bmR1.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.2");
            if (bmR3) bmR3.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.2");
            setOpacity(bmR1Pulse, 0);
            setOpacity(bmR3Pulse, 0);
            setFilter(bmR1Herald, residualGlow());
            setFilter(bmR3Herald, residualGlow());
            bsmQ.r1.forEach((q) => setFilter(q, residualGlow()));
            bsmQ.r3.forEach((q) => setFilter(q, residualGlow()));
            const elapsedMs = local - T_ES1_PREP - T_ES1_BSM;
            setOpacity(cbR1, 1); setOpacity(cbR3, 1);
            moveCbBySpeed("r1", elapsedMs);
            moveCbBySpeed("r3", elapsedMs);
          }
        }
        // -------- Phase 3 — 2nd ES --------
        else if (elapsed < (t0 += PHASE3)) {
          highlightStep(3);
          setOpacity(rows[0], 0.45);
          setOpacity(rows[1], 0.45);
          setOpacity(rows[2], 1);
          setOpacity(rows[3], 0.22);
          setOpacity(cbR1, 0); setOpacity(cbR3, 0);

          const local = elapsed - (t0 - PHASE3);
          if (local < T_ES2_PREP) {
            setOpacity(cbR2, 0);
            setOpacity(bmR2Pulse, 0); setFilter(bmR2Herald, "none");
            if (local < T_ES2_FADE) {
              const t = local / T_ES2_FADE;
              ent3.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("opacity", String(t)));
              ent3.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.7"));
            } else {
              const t = (local - T_ES2_FADE) / T_ES2_SETTLE;
              const w = 1.7 + 1.6 * Math.sin(t * Math.PI);
              ent3.forEach((p) => {
                if (!p) return;
                p.setAttribute("opacity", "1");
                p.setAttribute("stroke-width", String(w));
              });
            }
          } else if (local < T_ES2_PREP + T_ES2_BSM) {
            ent3.forEach((p) => {
              if (!p) return;
              p.setAttribute("opacity", "1");
              p.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.7");
            });
            const t = (local - T_ES2_PREP) / T_ES2_BSM;
            const pulse = Math.sin(t * Math.PI);
            const w = 1.2 + 1.6 * pulse;
            if (bmR2) bmR2.setAttribute("stroke-width", String(w));
            setOpacity(bmR2Pulse, pulse);
            const g2 = glow(pulse);
            setFilter(bmR2Herald, g2);
            bsmQ.r2.forEach((q) => setFilter(q, g2));
          } else {
            if (bmR2) bmR2.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.2");
            setOpacity(bmR2Pulse, 0);
            setFilter(bmR2Herald, residualGlow());
            bsmQ.r2.forEach((q) => setFilter(q, residualGlow()));
            const elapsedMs = local - T_ES2_PREP - T_ES2_BSM;
            setOpacity(cbR2, 1);
            moveCbBySpeed("r2", elapsedMs);
          }
        }
        // -------- Phase 4 — Result --------
        // Ramp the upper rows from 0.45 (history dim) back up to 1.0
        // across this phase so the transition into the "everything lit"
        // Hold scene is seamless.
        else if (elapsed < (t0 += PHASE4)) {
          highlightStep(4);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - PHASE4)) / PHASE4;
          const e = ease(Math.min(1, t));
          const upDim = 0.45 + 0.55 * e;
          setOpacity(rows[0], upDim);
          setOpacity(rows[1], upDim);
          setOpacity(rows[2], upDim);
          setOpacity(rows[3], 1);
          setOpacity(cbR2, 0);
          const localR = elapsed - (t0 - PHASE4);
          if (localR < T_RESULT_FADE) {
            const k = localR / T_RESULT_FADE;
            entFinal && entFinal.setAttribute("opacity", String(k));
            entFinal && entFinal.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.7");
          } else {
            const k = (localR - T_RESULT_FADE) / T_RESULT_SETTLE;
            const w = 1.7 + 1.6 * Math.sin(k * Math.PI);
            if (entFinal) {
              entFinal.setAttribute("opacity", "1");
              entFinal.setAttribute("stroke-width", String(w));
            }
          }
        }
        // -------- Hold --------
        // "Everything lit" final scene: all four rows at full opacity
        // with their end-state bonds drawn. This is the still-frame the
        // reader (or a playwright screenshot) lands on between cycles.
        else if (elapsed < T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE) {
          highlightStep(4);
          setOpacity(rows[0], 1);
          setOpacity(rows[1], 1);
          setOpacity(rows[2], 1);
          setOpacity(rows[3], 1);
          ent2.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("opacity", "1"));
          ent3.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("opacity", "1"));
          entFinal && entFinal.setAttribute("opacity", "1");
          // EG row: photons consumed, channels restored to full so the
          // row reads "ready for the next round" with the BSAs still
          // carrying a residual glow.
          resetFibresFull();
          resetWavyEmpty();
          photons.forEach((ph) => setOpacity(ph, 0));
          mpWaves.forEach((w) => setOpacity(w, 0));
          // Residual glow on every device (BSAs + BSM meters) and the
          // matter qubits that each meter measured.
          bsas.forEach((b, i) => setFilter(b, egSegs[i].heralded ? residualGlow() : "none"));
          setFilter(bmR1Herald, residualGlow());
          setFilter(bmR3Herald, residualGlow());
          setFilter(bmR2Herald, residualGlow());
          bsmQ.r1.forEach((q) => setFilter(q, residualGlow()));
          bsmQ.r3.forEach((q) => setFilter(q, residualGlow()));
          bsmQ.r2.forEach((q) => setFilter(q, residualGlow()));
        } else if (elapsed < T_TOTAL) {
          // Brief fade-out before the cycle resets so the transition into
          // the next round isn't a hard cut.
          const t = (elapsed - (T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE)) / T_PAUSE;
          const dim = 1 - t * 0.6;
          setOpacity(rows[0], dim);
          setOpacity(rows[1], dim);
          setOpacity(rows[2], dim);
          setOpacity(rows[3], dim);
        }
        updatePhaseLabel(elapsed);
      }

      // -------- Transport controls --------
      const btnPlay = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-ctl="play"]');
      const btnBack = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-ctl="back"]');
      const btnFwd  = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-ctl="fwd"]');
      const btnLoop = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-ctl="loop"]');
      const phaseLbl = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-phase]');

      // Loop-this-phase state. When ON, frame() wraps elapsed back to the
      // start of the phase whose index is loopPhaseIdx instead of advancing
      // to the next phase. Captured on toggle and updated by step buttons.
      let loopPhase = false;
      let loopPhaseIdx = 0;

      function updatePhaseLabel(elapsed) {
        if (phaseLbl) phaseLbl.textContent = phaseAt(elapsed);
      }
      function setPlayIcon() {
        if (btnPlay) {
          // Inline SVG icons — guaranteed monochrome on every platform.
          btnPlay.innerHTML = paused
            ? '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="18" height="18" aria-hidden="true">'
              + '<path d="M7 4v16l13-8z" fill="currentColor"/></svg>'
            : '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="18" height="18" aria-hidden="true">'
              + '<path d="M7 5h3v14H7zM14 5h3v14h-3z" fill="currentColor"/></svg>';
          btnPlay.setAttribute("aria-label", paused ? "Play" : "Pause");
        }
      }
      function setLoopIcon() {
        if (btnLoop) {
          btnLoop.setAttribute("aria-pressed", loopPhase ? "true" : "false");
        }
      }
      function currentElapsed(now) {
        if (paused) return pausedAt;
        let e = (now - cycleStart) * speed;
        if (e >= T_TOTAL) {
          // wrap inside frame() — but if asked here, normalise.
          e = e % T_TOTAL;
        }
        return e;
      }
      // PHASE_STARTS = [0, P1, P1+P2, P1+P2+P3, P1+P2+P3+P4].
      // Valid loop indices are 0..3 (the four protocol phases).
      // Index 4 marks the start of the post-Result Hold window — not a
      // protocol phase, so the loop should never capture it.
      const LAST_PHASE_IDX = PHASE_STARTS.length - 2;  // 3
      function currentPhaseIndex(elapsed) {
        for (let i = LAST_PHASE_IDX; i >= 0; i--) {
          if (elapsed >= PHASE_STARTS[i]) return i;
        }
        return 0;
      }
      function phaseEnd(idx) {
        // For the last protocol phase (Result), extend the loop window to
        // include the Hold time. Otherwise the wavy A↔B Bell pair would
        // retrace from invisible the instant it finishes drawing — the
        // user never sees the finished result before the next iteration
        // starts. Wrapping at T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE keeps the Hold-state view
        // visible for a beat before retrace.
        if (idx === LAST_PHASE_IDX) return T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE;
        return idx + 1 < PHASE_STARTS.length ? PHASE_STARTS[idx + 1] : T_TOTAL;
      }
      function togglePlay() {
        if (paused) {
          // Resume: shift cycleStart so elapsed reads pausedAt now.
          paused = false;
          cycleStart = performance.now() - pausedAt / speed;
        } else {
          // Pause: freeze the current virtual elapsed value.
          paused = true;
          pausedAt = (performance.now() - cycleStart) * speed;
          if (pausedAt < 0) pausedAt = 0;
          if (pausedAt >= T_TOTAL) pausedAt = T_TOTAL - 1;
        }
        setPlayIcon();
      }
      // Cycle playback speed: 0.5 → 0.75 → 1 → 0.5. Adjusts cycleStart
      // when running so the virtual clock stays continuous across the change.
      const SPEEDS = [0.5, 0.75, 1.0];
      function setSpeed(s) {
        if (!paused) {
          const cur = (performance.now() - cycleStart) * speed;
          speed = s;
          cycleStart = performance.now() - cur / speed;
        } else {
          speed = s;
        }
        setSpeedIcon();
      }
      function cycleSpeed() {
        const i = SPEEDS.indexOf(speed);
        setSpeed(SPEEDS[(i + 1) % SPEEDS.length]);
      }
      function setSpeedIcon() {
        const btn = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-ctl="speed"]');
        if (btn) btn.textContent = (speed === 1.0 ? "1×" : speed + "×");
      }
      function toggleLoop() {
        loopPhase = !loopPhase;
        if (loopPhase) {
          loopPhaseIdx = currentPhaseIndex(currentElapsed(performance.now()));
        }
        setLoopIcon();
      }
      function seekTo(t) {
        paused = true;
        pausedAt = Math.max(0, Math.min(T_TOTAL - 1, t));
        // Stepping while looping moves the loop to the new phase, so the
        // user can step then play and watch that phase on repeat.
        if (loopPhase) loopPhaseIdx = currentPhaseIndex(pausedAt);
        renderAt(pausedAt);
        setPlayIcon();
      }
      function stepForward() {
        const cur = currentElapsed(performance.now());
        const eps = 50;  // skip past the current boundary if we're right on one
        for (const b of PHASE_STARTS) {
          if (b > cur + eps) return seekTo(b);
        }
        // already past last phase start — wrap to start.
        seekTo(0);
      }
      function stepBackward() {
        const cur = currentElapsed(performance.now());
        const eps = 50;
        for (let i = PHASE_STARTS.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
          if (PHASE_STARTS[i] < cur - eps) return seekTo(PHASE_STARTS[i]);
        }
        seekTo(PHASE_STARTS[PHASE_STARTS.length - 1]);
      }
      const btnSpeed = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-ctl="speed"]');
      if (btnPlay) btnPlay.addEventListener("click", togglePlay);
      if (btnFwd)  btnFwd.addEventListener("click", stepForward);
      if (btnBack) btnBack.addEventListener("click", stepBackward);
      if (btnLoop) btnLoop.addEventListener("click", toggleLoop);
      if (btnSpeed) btnSpeed.addEventListener("click", cycleSpeed);
      setPlayIcon();
      setLoopIcon();
      setSpeedIcon();

      function frame(now) {
        if (paused) {
          // Hold the paused frame; keep ticking so unpausing resumes
          // cleanly without a stale render.
          renderAt(pausedAt);
        } else if (running) {
          let elapsed = (now - cycleStart) * speed;
          if (loopPhase) {
            const pStart = PHASE_STARTS[loopPhaseIdx];
            const pEnd   = phaseEnd(loopPhaseIdx);
            if (elapsed >= pEnd) {
              cycleStart = now - pStart / speed;
              elapsed = pStart;
            } else if (elapsed < pStart) {
              cycleStart = now - pStart / speed;
              elapsed = pStart;
            }
          } else if (elapsed >= T_TOTAL) {
            cycleStart = now;
            pickCycleParams();
            elapsed = 0;
          }
          renderAt(elapsed);
        }
        requestAnimationFrame(frame);
      }

      pickCycleParams();
      const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
        for (const entry of entries) {
          if (entry.isIntersecting && !running) {
            running = true;
            cycleStart = performance.now();
            pickCycleParams();
            requestAnimationFrame(frame);
          } else if (!entry.isIntersecting) {
            // Don't fully stop — user may have paused intentionally.
            // Only halt the auto-advance when the user hasn't paused.
            if (!paused) running = false;
          }
        }
      });
      observer.observe(fig);
      const handle = {
        teardown() {
          running = false;
          observer.disconnect();
        },
        // Render the "everything lit" Hold frame and freeze the engine
        // there. Used by the PNG download so the snapshot always lands
        // on the lit-up final scene rather than mid-animation.
        renderHold() {
          paused = true;
          pausedAt = T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE - 200;  // mid-Hold
          renderAt(pausedAt);
          setPlayIcon();
        },
      };
      fig.__onegenHandle = handle;
      return handle;
    }
    return { teardown() {} };
  }

  // Init every 1G figure on the page, then wire fullscreen + download.
  document.querySelectorAll("[data-1g]").forEach((fig) => {
    if (fig.dataset.onegenInited) return;
    fig.dataset.onegenInited = "1";
    initOnegen(fig);
  });

  // Snapshot the live SVG to a PNG at 2× the viewBox size, with a white
  // background. Inlines the computed style of every element from the live
  // SVG onto the clone so canvas-side rendering matches what the user
  // sees on the page (CSS variables, scoped Astro styles, etc. all
  // resolve to their final values).
  function downloadOnegenSvg(fig) {
    const svg = fig.querySelector("[data-1g-svg]");
    if (!svg) return;
    // Seek to the "everything lit" Hold frame so the snapshot is the
    // final scene rather than wherever the live animation happens to be.
    if (fig.__onegenHandle && fig.__onegenHandle.renderHold) {
      fig.__onegenHandle.renderHold();
    }
    const vb = svg.viewBox.baseVal;
    const w = vb.width || svg.clientWidth || 1100;
    const h = vb.height || svg.clientHeight || 600;
    const scale = 2;

    const clone = svg.cloneNode(true);
    clone.setAttribute("xmlns", "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg");
    clone.setAttribute("width", String(w));
    clone.setAttribute("height", String(h));

    // Properties that affect SVG visual rendering. Inlining these onto
    // every element makes the dataurl-rendered SVG self-contained.
    const visualProps = [
      "fill", "fill-opacity", "stroke", "stroke-opacity", "stroke-width",
      "stroke-linecap", "stroke-linejoin", "stroke-dasharray",
      "stroke-dashoffset", "opacity", "filter",
      "font-family", "font-size", "font-weight", "font-style",
      "text-anchor", "letter-spacing", "dominant-baseline",
    ];
    const srcEls = svg.querySelectorAll("*");
    const cloneEls = clone.querySelectorAll("*");
    for (let i = 0; i < srcEls.length; i++) {
      const cs = window.getComputedStyle(srcEls[i]);
      const inline = visualProps
        .map((p) => p + ":" + cs.getPropertyValue(p))
        .filter((s) => !s.endsWith(":") && !s.endsWith(":normal"))
        .join(";");
      const existing = cloneEls[i].getAttribute("style") || "";
      cloneEls[i].setAttribute("style", existing + ";" + inline);
    }

    const xml = new XMLSerializer().serializeToString(clone);
    const svg64 = btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(xml)));
    const dataUrl = "data:image/svg+xml;base64," + svg64;

    const img = new Image();
    img.onload = () => {
      const canvas = document.createElement("canvas");
      canvas.width = Math.round(w * scale);
      canvas.height = Math.round(h * scale);
      const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");
      ctx.fillStyle = "#ffffff";
      ctx.fillRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
      ctx.drawImage(img, 0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
      canvas.toBlob((blob) => {
        if (!blob) return;
        const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
        const a = document.createElement("a");
        a.href = url;
        a.download = "canonical-1g-repeater.png";
        document.body.appendChild(a);
        a.click();
        a.remove();
        URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
      }, "image/png");
    };
    img.onerror = () => {
      // Fallback: save the styled SVG so the user still gets something.
      const blob = new Blob([xml], { type: "image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8" });
      const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
      const a = document.createElement("a");
      a.href = url;
      a.download = "canonical-1g-repeater.svg";
      document.body.appendChild(a);
      a.click();
      a.remove();
      URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
    };
    img.src = dataUrl;
  }

  function openOnegenFullscreen(srcFig) {
    const dialog = document.createElement("dialog");
    dialog.className = "onegen-fullscreen";
    const clone = srcFig.cloneNode(true);
    delete clone.dataset.onegenInited;
    const fsBtn = clone.querySelector("[data-1g-fullscreen]");
    if (fsBtn) {
      const close = document.createElement("button");
      close.type = "button";
      close.className = fsBtn.className;
      close.setAttribute("aria-label", "Close full-screen view");
      close.setAttribute("title", "Close");
      close.innerHTML = '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="18" height="18" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M6 6l12 12M18 6l-12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>';
      close.addEventListener("click", () => dialog.close());
      fsBtn.parentNode.replaceChild(close, fsBtn);
    }
    dialog.appendChild(clone);
    document.body.appendChild(dialog);
    const handle = initOnegen(clone);
    dialog.addEventListener("close", () => {
      if (handle && handle.teardown) handle.teardown();
      dialog.remove();
    });
    dialog.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
      if (e.target === dialog) dialog.close();
    });
    dialog.showModal();
  }

  document.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
    const t = e.target;
    if (!t || !t.closest) return;
    const fsBtn = t.closest("[data-1g-fullscreen]");
    if (fsBtn) {
      const f = fsBtn.closest("[data-1g]");
      if (f) openOnegenFullscreen(f);
      return;
    }
    const dlBtn = t.closest("[data-1g-download]");
    if (dlBtn) {
      const f = dlBtn.closest("[data-1g]");
      if (f) downloadOnegenSvg(f);
    }
  });
</script>

